I disassembled the input station for the embedder sender C station. I checked the cylinder by actuating, and it looked consistent no air leaks. I checked the condition of the belt, cleaned the area of dust and debris. The vacuum filters behind the input station were also cleaned and reassembled. I found that the leveling disc was missing an anvil for the insertion process/module placement. I changed a bad suction cup and cleaned out the vacuum filter for the inserter. I also swapped the set screws for a different one that locks into the M3 pickup tool. I found on the inserter block that the top water fitting was leaking and I just replaced both of them due to the excessive wear and I trimmed the water line hoses back. I checked the actuation of the cutting block. That looked good as well. I cleaned and checked all presser head heights. Presser head #3 was the only one that needed to be adjusted and raised. All centering stations were checked and actuated. The depth checker was inspected and reset to zero without any issues. The machine was also vacuum for debris and loose modules.

I disassembled the input station for the milling station. I checked the cylinder by actuating, and it looked consistent no air leaks. I checked the condition of the belt, cleaned the area of dust and debris. I cleaned the suction cups, and I did notice the cards would bounce when pulling down. I made a height adjustment to alleviate the cards from bouncing up and down. The double card sensor works correctly. A thickness gauge pin was straightened out, and after testing the overall reset number was closer to zero. I remove all current offsets for the thickness & depth gauges. Everything resets properly. I checked all centering devices to ensure functionality. I replaced a cleaning belt on B cleaning station. I also made alignment adjustments to the positions of both cleaning stations as they were not leveled. The depth gauges had no issues. Output A & B cylinders are fine and work properly.

so, I had to think deep in the machine to find what is the cause of this issue.
so, I said the calibration is good, one head is cutting 15 good cards the other had is cutting bad cards, The table Y position is the same for both heads so I cannot change anything, the heads are cutting the same time.
The only Y position can be wrong the head itself!!!!
I remembered 5 weeks ago the pluritec engineer installed V3 spindles on this machine.
I was checking the spindles assembly and BINGO the spindle is loose!!!!!!!!!!!!!!
Tightened the spindle bolts run a sheet and it was good.
I asked the operators to run it and it is running good.
